         <fw type="continued" place="right"><date>January 26th 30</date></fw>
         <fw type="continued" place="left"><name ref="pers:CGS1">Mr. C. Gardner Sullivan</name></fw>
         <fw type="continued" place="left"><name ref="pers:WE1">Winnifred Reeve</name></fw>
         <fw type="continued" place="center">RE: <q>SCANDAL</q></fw>
<!-- Using fw to try to capture letter formatting. Using type=continued for now but is likely incorrect. -->
         <opener>
            <dateline>
               <date>January 26th 30</date>
            </dateline>
            <byline><name ref="pers:CGS1">Mr. C. Gardner Sullivan</name>
               <name ref="pers:WE1">Winnifred Reeve</name></byline>
         </opener>

         <div type="content">

            <p>RE: <q>SCANDAL</q></p>

            <p>I think this would make a dandy, sophisticated, smart and flashy story for <name
                  ref="pers:LLP1">Laura La Plante</name>.</p>
            <p>I dimly recall seeing the play - it was not so long ago at that, about four or five
               years ago and <q>SCANDAL</q> is more up-to-date than many of the new stories that are
               being written.</p>

         </div>
      </body>
